HEADWORD: Falx
<hw>Falx</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a sickle.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A curved fold or process of the <partof>dura
mater</partof> or the peritoneum; esp., one of the partitionlike folds
of the dura mater which extend into the great fissures of the
brain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

